The paper deals with complexity results for counting problems in graph theory and constraint satisfaction problems, which are typical topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of block interpolation and the focus on the number of acyclic subgraphs and independent sets suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of bipartite graphs and the Tutte polynomial may also indicate a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
